  "text": "The release profiles for gallic acid from the FCG nanocarrier in aqueous solution of 0.0001 M Na 2 CO 3 and phosphate-buff- was most likely due to the existence of coated materials and impurities on the surface of the magnetic nanoparticles. [CITATION_1] According to the vibrating sample magnetometry results, the nanoparticles showed superparamagnetic behavior, ie, they did not retain any magnetism after removal of the magnetic field. High magnetization and superparamagnetic properties are highly sought after for biomedical applications because the larger magnetic particles form aggregates after exposure to a magnetic field.",
